								<div class="title" id="post-title-4405932">
																		In just a moment, Vector will succumb to an illness worse than any virus can produce.
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ihp" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1267048); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1267048&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252528" alt="Ihp" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1267048)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ihp" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1267048); return false;" >Ihp</a></span> <span class="odate time_1571937623 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">24 Oct 2019 17:20</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4405932">
									

<p>So uh. I kind of got carried away with this.</p>
<p>This was honestly meant to just be a tale in which <a href="/scp-353">SCP-353</a> goes through a town-wide crisis on Halloween night. It evolved into a weird emotional character piece featuring her, Simon Glass, and a character mentioned in 353's file. I don't know <em>how</em>.</p>
<p>Some notes:</p>
<ul>
<li>SCP-353's file is <em>really</em> vague when it comes to physical description outside of her age, so that gave me plenty of wiggle room with regards to her race (she is meant to be African-American, I hope that comes across, and if not, apologies). In addition, I wrote a version of 353 for the SCP Origins RP back in 2014, so that helped form the basis of the character here. She was really flat, and it's been over a decade since the file was originally written, so I figured I should try to develop her.</li>
<li>For someone who hates old-school characters so much I seem to keep writing about them. Glass is one of the least-developed old-school characters on the wiki, so, again, that gave a lot of wiggle room.</li>
<li>Harkness is a nexus that's been in my head since I first started writing about Nexuses. It's, essentially, an anomalous leper colony&#8212; the people there are immune to everything from the common cold to athlete's foot, but somehow the town became a hotbed of supernatural diseases in the late 80's-early 90's.</li>
<li>Holy <em>shit</em> this went through a lot of iterations. There were at least two where Vector didn't appear at all, three where she was the antagonist and Audrey was a different character entirely who was a Foundation agent that just <em>happened</em> to be immuno-immaculate (another phrase I hate myself for coining) and eventually was transfigured into a new instance of 353 because the Foundation had to keep every slot full.</li>
<li>Thanks to several people for critting this, including <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rockteethmotheyes" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4022320); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4022320&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1571937623" alt="RockTeethMothEyes" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4022320)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rockteethmotheyes" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4022320); return false;">RockTeethMothEyes</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/calibri-bold" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5045819); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5045819&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1571937623" alt="Calibri Bold" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5045819)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/calibri-bold" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5045819); return false;">Calibri Bold</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dyslexion" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5549954); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5549954&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1571937623" alt="Dyslexion" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5549954)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dyslexion" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5549954); return false;">Dyslexion</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drchandra" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1956625); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1956625&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1571937623" alt="DrChandra" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1956625)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drchandra" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1956625); return false;">DrChandra</a></span>, and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/nozpot" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4065365); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4065365&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1571937623" alt="nozpot" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4065365)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/nozpot" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4065365); return false;">nozpot</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<p>Enjoy! I'll try to post more frequently now that I have time to write. This is my 99th tale, so Tale 100 is going to be cooking for a bit longer before I post it.</p>

