				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sergeimosin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1652931); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1652931&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252528" alt="Sergeimosin" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1652931)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sergeimosin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1652931); return false;" >Sergeimosin</a></span> <span class="odate time_1571955675 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">24 Oct 2019 22:21</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4406101">
									

<p>I feel like this is more effective as a stand alone character piece than it is as a black autumn tale, and here's for why: the effect was overly localized and doesn't seem to have effected the town at large.</p>
<p>Now, mind you, this is a SUPERB evolution of the SCP in question (turning it from a generic self insert X-man to a 3 dimensional character could not have been an easy task, but it was deftly handled), but I feel like the scope needs to widen quite a bit to be a proper Black Autumn as opposed to just another weird thursday.</p>
<p>Now, having said that, if the golden apples (nice Eris reference, by the by) happened to find their way around town and cause all sorts of chaos, I could see this being it's own self contained mini anthology within an anthology, which could be a seriously interesting ride.</p>
<p>Anyway, +1 for turning the literary equivalent of steakums into the equivalent of a well aged, perfectly seasoned filet paired with a good stout (I need to stop reviewing things when I'm hungry)</p>

							</div>

								
					
